{"type":"message","id":"2271424e","parentId":"634e660b","timestamp":"2026-04-26T05:10:48.827Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ollama is running but all the models are \"cloud\" models - they don't run locally, they connect to cloud APIs. This means they won't use GPU memory, which is actually good for the user's situation.\n\nLet me check which model would be good to use. The user has cloud models in Ollama, so switching to Ollama won't actually free up GPU memory since these are cloud models. But the issue is that lm_studio is using GPU memory for running local models.\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. The user wants to:\n1. Free up GPU memory so ComfyUI can run\n\n\n2. Still be able to chat with me\n\nSwitching to Ollama with cloud models would let me keep chatting while freeing up the GPU memory that lm_studio is consuming for local model inference. The cloud models won't need GPU resources, so this solves both problems. I should pick a capable cloud model from the list and add Ollama as a provider to the config.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nOllama 启动了，不过你拉的全是 cloud 模型（走云端 API，不吃本地显存）。这正好 —— 切到 Ollama 后 lm_studio 可以关了，显存就释放了。\n\n我用 `gpt-oss:120b-cloud` 作为主力模型（120B 参数，很强）。现在改配置：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"829846257","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.patch","raw":"{\n  \"models\": {\n    \"providers\": {\n      \"ollama\": {\n        \"baseUrl\": \"http://127.0.0.1:11434/v1\",\n        \"apiKey\": \"ollama\",\n        \"api\": \"openai-completions\",\n        \"models\": [\n          {\n            \"id\": \"gpt-oss:120b-cloud\",\n            \"name\": \"ollama / GPT-OSS 120B Cloud\",\n            \"input\": [\"text\"],\n            \"contextWindow\": 131072,\n            \"maxTokens\": 32768\n          }\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"agents\": {\n    \"defaults\": {\n      \"models\": {\n        \"ollama/gpt-oss:120b-cloud\": {}\n      },\