{"type":"message","id":"7824eb73","parentId":"7407513a","timestamp":"2026-04-26T07:38:50.056Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to generate a image using ComfyUI based on provided reference image, but ComfyUI server is not running. We might need to start it. There's a UI script requiring term. Might need to run via exec with pty? However we can try to start ComfyUI in background with exec background true. Then wait. Then use the appropriate workflow? Could use a simple generation: load image, use controlnet to apply? But we don't have a workflow file. Could use a simple generate via text-to-image? Might need a model. Not sure.\n\nSimplify: maybe we can just respond that ComfyUI not running and ask to start? But user wants image. Could suggest using Ollama model to generate description? Probably need to run ComfyUI.\n\nWe can attempt to start ComfyUI: exec \"comfyui --listen 0.0.0.0 --port 8188\" with pty. Use background. Then after start, maybe we can use API to generate. But not enough time.\n\nBetter to ask user to start ComfyUI or we can spawn a sub-agent to handle image generation? Could spawn a subagent with \"runtime: subagent\" and a skill? But we don't have a skill for ComfyUI. Could use a browser automation to click? Too complex.\n\nGiven constraints, maybe we should respond that ComfyUI is not running and ask to start it, or we can attempt to start it.\n\nWe can start ComfyUI in background: exec with background true. Use pty false? It's a TUI, but maybe works. Let's try."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_472bbc70-8701-4095-93dc-217f55a33f7f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"comfyui --listen 0.0.0.0 --port 8188","background":true,"pty":false,"ask":"off","host":"auto","elevated":false,"timeout":600000}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama","model":"gpt-oss:120b-cloud","usage":{"input":57968,"output":396,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58364,"cost":{"input":0