{"type":"message","id":"731e8ff6","parentId":"a2295339","timestamp":"2026-04-26T07:40:33.155Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to generate a beautiful woman image using the provided screenshot as reference. They expect the assistant to operate ComfyUI to generate the image. We have started ComfyUI with listen on port 8188. Need to interact with ComfyUI via its API or web UI. Likely use the API endpoints. ComfyUI has a REST API: e.g., POST /prompt to run a workflow. Need to build a JSON workflow: nodes like \"Load Image\", \"Stable Diffusion\", \"Save Image\". Also we can use \"KSampler\" etc. We need to produce an image based on the reference. Possibly use \"img2img\". We need to send a workflow JSON to ComfyUI's /prompt endpoint. Let's create a minimal workflow:\n\nNodes:\n0: LoadImage (image path)\n1: CLIPTextEncode (positive prompt)\n2: CLIPTextEncode (negative prompt)\n3: KSampler (model: sd_xl_base_1.0.safetensors maybe; but we need a model file path; maybe they have any model loaded automatically? Not sure. Could use \"Stable Diffusion XL\" but need model name. Might use \"sdxl-base-1.0\". For simplicity, we can use \"Stable Diffusion v1-5\"? Not known. We could just call \"img2img\" using \"Image2Image\" node.\n\nSimplify: Use \"Image2Image (img2img)\" node that takes init_image and prompts.\n\nComfyUI API: The node IDs are strings, type, inputs. Could look up typical JSON example. Let's search web quickly."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_c85c540f-7f5d-4e50-9af3-bf178c778c8e","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/comfyanonymous/ComfyUI/master/docs/api.md","extractMode":"text","maxChars":2000}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama","model":"gpt-oss:120b-cloud","usage":{"input":58798,"output":383,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59181,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":17771892