{"type":"message","id":"6ee6da12","parentId":"a372eda7","timestamp":"2026-04-26T07:45:45.878Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The unet and vae folders are empty - this means there are no local diffusion models installed. ComfyUI is using the sd3.5_medium model which is in the checkpoints folder.\n\nComfyUI has a REST API for queuing prompts. Let me write a Python script that:\n1. Uses the ComfyUI REST API to queue a prompt\n2. Monitors the progress\n3. Returns the output image path\n\nThe API works by:\n1. POST to /prompt with a workflow JSON\n2. The response includes a prompt_id\n3. Poll /history/{prompt_id} to get the status and output images\n\n\n4. Now I'm looking at the sd3.5_medium model structure in checkpoints to understand how it's organized.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_e91bddc5-6641-43c5-a129-4a3d80be50fc","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8188/api/stats 2>/dev/null && echo \"---\" && ls /home/kensoulstar/ComfyUI/output/ 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":67852,"output":226,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68078,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1777189545878}}
