{"type":"message","id":"8c324524","parentId":"7207d310","timestamp":"2026-04-26T07:49:01.413Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"KSampler outputs LATENT (a latent image), and VAEDecode requires \"samples\" as input. The workflow needs to connect KSampler's LATENT output to VAEDecode's \"samples\" input, not \"sample\". Let me fix this.\n\nThe node IDs in the workflow are just identifiers. The connection between nodes is done by referencing the correct output from one node as input to another. The key names in the inputs dict must match the node's input names.\n\nSo:\n- KSampler outputs: LATENT\n- VAEDecode requires: \"samples\" \n\nWhen we write `[\"7\", 0]` in VAEDecode's input, it means \"take output index 0 from node 7 (KSampler)\". The KSampler's output at index 0 is LATENT. So `[\"7\", 0]` in the \"samples\" field of VAEDecode correctly maps to the LATENT output.\n\n\nBut the error says KSampler has output at index 0 being LATENT, and I'm using `[\"7\", 0]` for VAEDecode's \"samples\" input. That should work unless there's something else wrong with the workflow structure.\n\nLet me just execute it and see what happens."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_13970719-2771-4779-9ea1-7f3625a16739","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/kensoulstar/ComfyUI && source venv/bin/activate && python3 -c \"\nimport requests, json\n\n# KSampler -> VAEDecode 用 samples 连接\nworkflow = {\n    '3': {\n        'class_type': 'CheckpointLoaderSimple',\n        'inputs': {'ckpt_name': 'sd3.5_medium.safetensors'}\n    },\n    '4': {\n        'class_type': 'CLIPTextEncode',\n        'inputs': {\n            'text': 'portrait of a beautiful woman, sharp facial features, soft lighting, cinematic detail, high quality, photorealistic',\n            'clip': ['3', 0]\n        }\n    },\n    '5': {\n        'class_type': 'CLIPTextEncode',\n        'inputs': {\n            'text': 'low quality, blurry, distortion, bad anatomy, deformed, ugly',\n            'clip': ['3', 1]\n        }\n    },\n    '6': {\n        'class_type': 'LoadImage',\n        'inputs': {'image': 'ref.png'}\n    },\n    '7': {\n        'class_type': 'KSampler',\n        'inputs': {\n            'model': ['3', 0],\n            'seed': 12345,\n            'steps': 25,\n            'cfg': 7.0,\n            'sampler_name': 'euler',\n            'scheduler': 'normal',\n            'positive': ['4', 0],\n            'negative': ['5', 0],\n            'denoise': 0.7\n        }\n    },\n    '8': {\n        'class_type': 'VAEDecode',\n        'inputs': {\n            'samples': ['7', 0],  # KSampler输出 LATENT(index 0) -> VAEDecode输入 samples\n            'vae': ['3', 2]\n        }\n    },\n    '9': {\n        'class_type': 'SaveImage',\n        'inputs': {'images': ['8', 0], 'filename_prefix': 'gen_beauty'}\n    }\n}\n\nr = requests.post('http://127.0.0.1:8188/prompt', json={'prompt': workflow}, timeout=10)\nprint('Submit:', r.status_code)\nif r.status_code != 200:\n    print('Error:', r.text[:400])\nelse:\n    data = r.json()\n    pid = data.get('prompt_id')\n    print('prompt_id:', pid)\n\""}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":74002,"output":791,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74793,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1777189741412}}
