{"type":"message","id":"8df16ba8","parentId":"76f0900a","timestamp":"2026-04-26T07:49:14.023Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that \"CLIPTextEncode\" takes a \"clip\" input which should be CLIP type, but I'm connecting `[\"3\", 0]` which is the MODEL output from CheckpointLoaderSimple, not the CLIP output. \n\nIn ComfyUI's CheckpointLoaderSimple:\n- Output 0 = MODEL\n- Output 1 = CLIP\n- Output 2 = VAE\n\nSo CLIPTextEncode should use `[\"3\", 1]` for the clip input. Let me also check what \"CLIPTextEncode\" expects as input.\n\nActually wait - the error says \"received_type(MODEL) mismatch input_type(CLIP)\" for \"clip\" input. \n\nSo I need to fix the connection by using index 1 on the CheckpointLoader output instead of index 0, and I should verify the VAEDecode node's requirements as well."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_0b7522fb-4d30-4b94-9660-df14efc02350","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/kensoulstar/ComfyUI && source venv/bin/activate && python3 -c \"\nimport requests, json\n\n# CheckpointLoaderSimple: 0=MODEL, 1=CLIP, 2=VAE\n# CLIPTextEncode 需要 CLIP (index 1)，不是 MODEL (index 0)\nworkflow = {\n    '3': {\n        'class_type': 'CheckpointLoaderSimple',\n        'inputs': {'ckpt_name': 'sd3.5_medium.safetensors'}\n    },\n    '4': {\n        'class_type': 'CLIPTextEncode',\n        'inputs': {\n            'text': 'portrait of a beautiful woman, sharp facial features, soft lighting, cinematic detail, high quality, photorealistic',\n            'clip': ['3', 1]  # CLIP output (index 1)\n        }\n    },\n    '5': {\n        'class_type': 'CLIPTextEncode',\n        'inputs': {\n            'text': 'low quality, blurry, distortion, bad anatomy, deformed, ugly',\n            'clip': ['3', 1]\n        }\n    },\n    '6': {\n        'class_type': 'LoadImage',\n        'inputs': {'image': 'ref.png'}\n    },\n    '7': {\n        'class_type': 'KSampler',\n        'inputs': {\n            'model'