{"type":"message","id":"1390470c","parentId":"8afc069a","timestamp":"2026-04-26T07:50:12.381Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error is: \"ERROR: clip input is invalid: None. If the clip is from a checkpoint loader node your checkpoint does not contain a valid clip or text encoder model.\"\n\nThis means the `sd3.5_medium.safetensors` model doesn't have a valid CLIP text encoder. This is a common issue with newer SD3 models - they use a different CLIP architecture (MMDiT). For SD3, you need to use `DualCLIPLoader` instead of `CLIPTextEncode` with a single CLIP.\n\nLet me check what models are available and what nodes they support.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_1d099d53-6814-4bff-89c5-797c6abf37ba","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/kensoulstar/ComfyUI && source venv/bin/activate && python3 -c \"\nimport requests, json\n\n# 检查 DualCLIPLoader\nr = requests.get('http://127.0.0.1:8188/object_info/DualCLIPLoader', timeout=10)\ndcl = r.json()['DualCLIPLoader']\nprint('DualCLIPLoader input required:', list(dcl['input']['required'].keys()))\n\n# 检查 SD3 模型需要什么样的 loader\nr2 = requests.get('http://127.0.0.1:8188/object_info/CheckpointLoaderSimple', timeout=10)\ncl = r2.json()['CheckpointLoaderSimple']\nprint('CheckpointLoaderSimple input required:', list(cl['input']['required'].keys()))\n\""}}],"stopReason":"toolUse","api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama","model":"minimax-m2.7:cloud","usage":{"input":78508,"output":308,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78816,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1777189812381}}
