{"type":"message","id":"711e00d8","parentId":"40427017","timestamp":"2026-04-26T07:50:22.996Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that `sd3.5_medium.safetensors` is a SD3.5 model and needs separate clip models (via `DualCLIPLoader`), not from `CheckpointLoaderSimple`. The `CheckpointLoaderSimple` for SD3 models needs different handling.\n\nBut this is getting complex. Let me instead just check what models are available that work with the simple loader.\n\nActually, let me think about what I know:\n- The `sd3.5_medium.safetensors` file exists in checkpoints\n- It needs separate CLIP loading\n- This is getting into deep ComfyUI/SD3 configuration territory\n\n\n- Rather than debugging the model setup, I could try using the Manager interface to load the model properly, or just verify that the LoRA/moderation models in the directory would work with the straightforward `CheckpointLoaderSimple` approach.\n\nActually, the core problem is that sd3.5 requires dual CLIP loaders since it has a different architecture than SD1.5 models. I could either find a compatible SD1.5/SDXL checkpoint that's already in the directory, or explore the API endpoints to see if there's a simpler way to load the model through the ComfyUI manager.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ollama_call_db377467-c4c0-4a8f-a4da-8435da1c593e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/kensoulstar/ComfyUI && source venv/bin/activate && python3 -c \"\nimport requests, json\n\n# 检查 sd3.5 模型需要的 loader 类型\nr = requests.get('http://127.0.0.1:8188/object_info/STABLE_DIFFUSION_3', timeout=10)\nprint('SD3 loader:', r.status_code, list(r.json().keys()) if r.status_code==200 else 'not found')\n\n# 找 SDXL 的 loader\nfor name in ['StableDiffusion3Scheduler', 'SD3TextEncode']:\n    r = requests.get(f'http://127.0.0.1:8188/object_info/{name}', timeout=10)\n    print(name, ':', r.status_code)\n\n# 看看 examples 目录或 workflow 文件\nimport os\nfor root, dirs, files in os.walk('/home/ken